    {
        "content": "<p>Here’s what I found:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Matrix.mulVec_add#doc\">For any $m \\times n$ matrix $A$ over a type $\\alpha$ (where $n$ is finite) and any two vectors $x, y : n \\to \\alpha$, the matrix-vector multiplication is additive in the vector argument:\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi><msub><mo>∗</mo><mi>v</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><msub><mo>∗</mo><mi>v</mi></msub><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>A</mi><msub><mo>∗</mo><mi>v</mi></msub><mi>y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> A *ᵥ (x + y) = A *ᵥ x + A *ᵥ y </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">v</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">v</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">v</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span></span></span></span>\nwhere $*ᵥ$ denotes matrix-vector multiplication.</a> (score: 0.734)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Matrix.mulVec_add#doc\">For any $m \\times n$ matrix $A$ over a type $\\alpha$ (where $n$ is finite) and any two vectors $x, y : n \\to \\alpha$, the matrix-vector multiplication is additive in the vector argument:\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi><msub><mo>∗</mo><mi>v</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><msub><mo>∗</mo><mi>v</mi></msub><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>A</mi><msub><mo>∗</mo><mi>v</mi></msub><mi>y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> A *ᵥ (x + y) = A *ᵥ x + A *ᵥ y </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">v</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">v</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">v</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span></span></span></span>\nwhere $*ᵥ$ denotes matrix-vector multiplication.</a> (score: 0.731)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=LinearMap.sum_apply#doc\">Let $ι$ be a type, $t$ be a finite subset of $ι$, and $f : ι \\to \\text{Hom}_σ(M, M₂)$ be a family of semilinear maps between $R$-module $M$ and $S$-module $M₂$ with respect to a ring homomorphism $σ : R \\to S$. Then for any $b \\in M$, the evaluation of the sum of these maps at $b$ equals the sum of their evaluations at $b$, i.e.,\n\\[\n\\left(\\sum_{d \\in t} f_d\\right)(b) = \\sum_{d \\in t} f_d(b).\n\\]</a> (score: 0.728)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Matrix.add_vecMul#doc\">Let $m$ be a finite index type, $A$ be an $m \\times n$ matrix over a type $\\alpha$, and $x, y$ be vectors in $m \\to \\alpha$. Then the vector-matrix multiplication satisfies the linearity property $(x + y) \\ ᵥ* \\ A = x \\ ᵥ* \\ A + y \\ ᵥ* \\ A$.</a> (score: 0.720)</p>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Matrix.mulVecLin_add#doc\">For any finite type $n$ and matrices $M, N \\in \\text{Matrix}(m \\times n, R)$ over a commutative ring $R$, the linear map associated with the sum of $M$ and $N$ is equal to the sum of the linear maps associated with $M$ and $N$ individually. That is, $\\text{mulVecLin}(M + N) = \\text{mulVecLin}(M) + \\text{mulVecLin}(N)$.</a> (score: 0.720)</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=LinearMap.map_sum₂#doc\">Let $M$, $N$, and $P$ be modules over rings with semilinear structures given by ring homomorphisms $\\rho_{12} \\colon R \\to R_2$ and $\\sigma_{12} \\colon S \\to S_2$. For any bilinear map $f \\colon M \\to_{[\\rho_{12}]} N \\to_{[\\sigma_{12}]} P$, any finite index set $\\iota$, any function $x \\colon \\iota \\to M$, and any element $y \\in N$, the following equality holds:\n\\[ f\\left(\\sum_{i \\in t} x_i\\right) y = \\sum_{i \\in t} f(x_i) y. \\]</a> (score: 0.716)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Matrix.add_vecMul#doc\">For any matrix $A$ of size $m \\times n$ over a type $\\alpha$ (where $m$ is finite) and any two vec